<TITLE> Sri Lankan rebel bomb kills 15, wounds 25-military </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 COLOMBO, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A roadside bomb planted by Sri Lankan Tamil Tiger rebels killed 15 people and wounded 25 on Wednesday, the military said. Military spokesman Brigadier Udaya Nanayakkara said the bomb targeted a crowded civilian bus in the north-central district of Anuradhapura.
